---
title: Szechuan Chicken & Broccoli-Carrot Stir-Fry with Rice & Peanuts
description: A few key ingredients transform this humble vegan stir-fry into something special—all in a quick 20 minutes! You’ll sizzle broccoli, carrots, and onion in a hot skillet, then toss with sweet soy glaze and spicy Szechuan paste, plus a little vinegar for contrast. Serve it all over fluffy rice with a sprinkle of crunchy peanuts.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6655f66d8a4eed4f27b52fc7-6640b31e.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66c625055cb721784e6384a6-en-US.pdf
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: East Asia
time required: 20 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 17 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 93 g
  sugar: 28 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1460 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/szechuan-chicken-and-broccoli-carrot-stir-fry-66c625055cb721784e6384a6
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄4-inch-thick pieces (halve lengthwise first if carrots are on the larger side). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Rinse shrimp under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}, or open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add shrimp or chicken in a single layer; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add carrots; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add onion and broccoli; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until onion is translucent and broccoli is tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> Use pan used for shrimp or chicken here.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, half the @Szechuan paste{2%tablespoon}, half the @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 3/4 cup water, and @sugar{1%teaspoon}.

> For 4 servings, use all the Szechuan paste, all the vinegar, 11⁄2 cups water, and 2 tsp sugar.

Add Szechuan sauce (reserve bowl; no need to wipe out!) and @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} to pan with stir-fry. Cook, stirring, until everything is thoroughly coated in sauce, ~{1-2%minutes}.

In bowl used for sauce, mix @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} with 1 TBSP water until dissolved.

Stir cornstarch mixture into stir-fry until fully incorporated; simmer until sauce thickens, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> We used 1⁄8 tsp chili flakes; 1⁄4 tsp for 4 servings. TIP: If sauce is too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Stir in shrimp or chicken along with chili flakes.

Massage rice in package to break up grains. Partially open package; microwave @microwaveable jasmine rice{1} until warmed through, ~{1½-2%minutes}.

> Careful when handling and opening the pouch!

Transfer rice to a #medium bowl{} and fluff with a #fork{}.

Divide rice and stir-fry between plates in separate sections. Sprinkle with @peanuts{½%ounce} and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.